         <div type="translation">
            <p>Hegeso daughter of Proxenios.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>Transcription from photo. The modern plaster cast is a replica of IG I, 3rd ed., 1289, an Attic grave stele dated to the last decade of the fifth century BCE.  Within the naisokos are depicted in relief a seated woman (presumably Hegeso) wearing a chiton and himation with her feet resting on a stool. In her left hand she reaches toward a pyxis held out to her by a maidservant dressed in a tunic and headdress standing before her. The cast is hung in the entrance hallway of the long-time home of the Classics Department at Brown University, MacFarlane House, at 48 College Street.</p>
         </div>
